ce:section.ce:para:
Fig. 2
 displays the nanostructure of the materials recorded by scanning electron microscopy (SEM). As seen in MoS2/CQD and MoS2/CQD/Ag nanocomposites, the presence of amorphous CQDs on the flowerlike structures of MoS2 has changed their structures. In addition, the presence of dendritic Ag and amorphous CQDs besides the flowerlike structure of MoS2 confirm the successful synthesis of MoS2/CQD/Ag nanocomposite. TEM and EDS analyses were used to characterize MoS2/CQD/Ag nanocomposite (Fig. 3
). TEM image clearly showed the dendritic structure of Ag, nanosheets of flowerlike MoS2, and CQDs. Qualitative EDS analysis shows that all the elements C, O, Mo, S, and Ag exist in MoS2/CQD/Ag nanocomposite.
